com.hannesdorfmann.mosby3.mvp.delegate

Class FragmentMvpDelegateImpl<V extends MvpView,P extends MvpPresenter<V>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hannesdorfmann.mosby3.mvp.delegate.FragmentMvpDelegateImpl<V,P>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - The type of MvpView
    P - The type of MvpPresenter
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    FragmentMvpDelegate<V,P>

    public class FragmentMvpDelegateImpl<V extends MvpView,P extends MvpPresenter<V>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements FragmentMvpDelegate<V,P>
    The default implementation of FragmentMvpDelegate Presenter is available (has view attached) in onViewCreated(View, Bundle) (after called super.onViewCreated()). View will be detached in onDestroyView() from presenter, and eventually presenter will be destroyed in onDestroy().
    Since:
    1.1.0
    See Also:
    FragmentMvpDelegate
